KMP Public Server Collection

(if anyone wants to take this over and start a new thread, they are free to do so)

Here you can post your KMP Public Servers.

I don't have a KMP Server but i noticed that servers were all over the place, on the signatures on the main thread and all in between.

Here is a dedicated thread for the inevitable hordes of servers that will come.

(As of now, i cant test if these are great servers yet, so it would be nice i anybody tested them to make sure they are still good, been about a month since last post.)

Welcome, and post away!

I will put a few servers that pop up right in this post. I probably won't go over 10 in the post, to avoid clutter inside it.

Modded Servers are welcome! (please post mods used)

Edit: Please post your continent or nation you are hosting from. You can be more specific if you want. It would be appreciated if you also add status update pages and i will add them where your server is listed.

Here is a server list website people can use: http://servers.kerbalcentral.com (currently only has a few)

Nations Server

Basic idea of this:

Fight or ally other space nations on different planets.

Some planets may be controlled by someone or may be controlled by no one.

Kerbin is a neutral planet. No one can claim it, but fights can go on in it.

Do random science to learn new things like how to make an artificial Kerbal Grabber, or just a simple satellite meant to protect your planet system and or attack others.

When you learn something new, you can use it against your enemies or allies (if you want to back-stab them). This isn't career mode, by science I mean building things to learn new ways to kill.

Rules:

1. No claiming other planets unless they have no flag or are conquered by someone.

2. Place a flag to capture a planet, it must be empty of any other players.

3. You must declare who is an ally in the chat.

4. You can use cheats, as this isn't meant for actual science but rather war!

5. Whack-a-Kerbal is considered an actual cheat. If you are reported and found to use it, you will be kicked from the server along with your things.

6. Maximum of 5 players due to lag constraints.

7. You can do negotiations and trade things.

Max Players: 5

IP: 174.69.34.49

Port: 55905

Compatible Mods: MechJeb, HyperEdit, and Firespitter Aircraft Parts

Max Nations: 5

Other Notes: Any bugs must be reported to me AND the mod developers of KMP.
